<br>
<br>
No, it is definitely RAW HP gear.  Anything with HP 30 or whatever on it.  I'm intimately aware of this problem, as my gnome supertwink couldn't zone at less than 50% health until he was almost 40, from wearing well over 500 HP on his gear.<br>
<br>
I have never seen this be a 'blessing', the whole 'you would have died but you didn't' is bullshit.  It's a bug from the system substracting not knowing how much HP is on your gear during the zone.  You weren't going to die, you didn't die zoning, you just had on gear.<br>
<br>
The only times I've ever seen it do something positive besides stripping your buffs for zoning is when people ABUSE it by zoning off dots, rez effects, and the like.  (Loot up and leaves the planes, presto chango no rez effects cause the GY is often right by the click out), or use it to regain health (I've seen shaman do this with canni/zone and pop up with half health on the other side).<br>
<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm just bitter from constantly losing KEI in backassward no where from zoning at 450HP with NO AGRO on me at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fraethir>Fraethir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 769<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/20/03 10:00:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25980.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is this still happening?</span><hr size=1> No, it's a blessing.<br>
<br>
When the server thinks you're dead, and the client thinks you're alive, there's often a compromise reached (which is you being at the safepoint, or rolled back to a recent save point 'your game has been saved', or completing the zoning with no buffs (but alive).<br>
<br>
And the REASON it's a blessing? Without it, you'd have GatedButDead syndrome all over the place. When your client thinks you've zoned out, you may still be in-zone for the server (and thus for the mobs). You might think you have 'plenty' of hp, but you could easy rack up immense damage during however long you're standing there getting beat up before the server finally subtracts you from the zone.<br>
<br>
While quadding, I've gone from 100% hp and a rune, to showing up naked at my bindpoint and dead, from a gate completing while a horde of mobs were rushing me. Whenever I zone out ahead of a crowd by running the zoneline, and come out with buffs stripped, I'm GLAD. I lived. =P<br>
<br>
There are three things that can happen with zoning weirdness, the one where too much raw +hp screws your buffs up is only one and only really a consequence for those who benefit a LOT from mudflation or twinking. <br>
#1: Zone with fewer hp than your raw hp gear: HP gear is added after zoning, like the faction tables (as far as I know, when you zone you come in with however many hp you've got... minus the hp gear. Just like you can KILL yourself by taking off hp gear when critically hurt. I've pulled this off with a monk, when I was bandaging and sleepy.<br>
#2/3: Start zoning 'alive'. Server thinks you've died for one of many reasons. Two options: It sets you back in the same zone at the safepoint or your last 'savepoint' (I've had this happen running out of lavastorm when I was little. I hit the zoneline at like, 10hp. . . then was suddenly back in the zone BEHIND the elementals that were beating me up (with about 110 hp instead of 10), had to charge through them again which didn't work at all... or finish the zone stripped of buffs. I'd rather have the second happen, due to the survival.<br>
It's really, really minor for inconveniences, especially compared to the benefit you're getting from +hp gear. It's good for you, suck it up. The only time getting rebuffed is more irritating than dying is if you're wearing buffs vastly beyond your level, are majorly twinked, or have a 96% res at call any time, anywhere.<br>
